---
import Docs from '../../layouts/Docs.astro';

const toc = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'current-state', text: 'Current State', level: 2 },
  { id: 'planned', text: 'Planned Features', level: 2 },
];
---

<Docs title="Daemon & Sessions" toc={toc}>
  <div class="roadmap-banner">
    <strong>Daemon mode and session persistence are on the roadmap and not yet implemented.</strong>
    <p>ori-term currently runs in single-process mode. See the <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/roadmap`}>roadmap</a> for status.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>ori-term will eventually keep shell sessions running in a background process, separate from the window. Close the window and sessions keep running. Reopen and pick up where you left off. Similar to tmux's client-server model, but built into the terminal.</p>

  <h2 id="current-state">Current State</h2>
  <p>ori-term currently runs as a single process. Closing the window ends all shell sessions. Split tree undo/redo history is maintained during the session but is not persisted across restarts.</p>

  <h2 id="planned">Planned Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Background daemon</strong> — sessions survive after GUI closes</li>
    <li><strong>Auto-save</strong> — periodic saves of window positions, tabs, pane layout, and working directories</li>
    <li><strong>Crash recovery</strong> — detect unexpected exits and offer to restore the session</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-client</strong> — multiple windows connecting to the same daemon</li>
    <li><strong>Scrollback archive</strong> — disk-backed scrollback that survives restarts</li>
  </ul>
</Docs>

<style>
  .roadmap-banner {
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, transparent);
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .roadmap-banner strong {
    color: var(--accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .roadmap-banner p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
